{"id":6308,"date":"2016-06-30T15:03:42","date_gmt":"2016-06-30T15:03:42","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=6308"},"modified":"2019-07-15T11:43:02","modified_gmt":"2019-07-15T11:43:02","slug":"devtest-labs-security-settings","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/","title":{"rendered":"DevTest Labs security settings"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"#Intro\">Introduction<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 1\">Step 1: Add new User in DevTest Labs<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 2\">Step 2: Add Owner in DevTest Labs<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Con\">Conclusion<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h3 id=\"Intro\">Introduction<\/h3>\n<p>I\u2019ve described very in general what <strong>DevTest Labs policies<\/strong> are in previous blog post <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/29\/quick-overview-of-azure-devtest-labs\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Quick overview of Azure DevTest Labs<\/a>. Access for <strong>DevTest Labs<\/strong> is controlled by <a href=\"https:\/\/azure.microsoft.com\/en-us\/updates\/general-availability-role-based-access-control\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Azure Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you are the owner of specific Lab you can apply security access setting by two lab roles: <strong>Owner<\/strong> and <strong>User DevTest Lab Role<\/strong>. The <strong>Owner<\/strong> role has a full access including management and monitoring functions. Here is very important to emphasize the importance between those roles in lab. If the owner has assigned <strong>User<\/strong> lab role, this role doesn\u2019t have the permissions to access resources in the subscription outside the lab scope. But in the opposite case, when the <strong>User<\/strong> is assigned to <strong>Owner<\/strong> role, he can automatically have the <strong>Owner<\/strong> rights to all created resources in that subscription.<\/p>\n<p><strong>User<\/strong> role is very limited. This role can only create <strong>VM\u2019s<\/strong>, delete only his <strong>VM\u2019s<\/strong> and connect only to his created <strong>VM\u2019s<\/strong>.<br \/>\nThis post will describe step by step tutorial for setting <strong>DevTest Labs security settings<\/strong> and detailed description of role functionalities.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip<\/span> If you would like to know more about this new developer service available on the <a href=\"https:\/\/azure.microsoft.com\/en-gb\/\">Azure<\/a> platform, you can have a look at the following post; <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/12\/more-about-azure-devtest-labs\/\">More about Azure DevTest Labs<\/a>. If you prefer a more concise description of the same feature, &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/29\/quick-overview-of-azure-devtest-labs\/\">have a look at Quick overview of Azure DevTest Labs<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Step 1\">Step 1: Add new User in DevTest Labs<\/h3>\n<p>User can be either internal user with <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/azure.microsoft.com\/en-us\/pricing\/details\/active-directory\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Azure Active Directory subscription<\/a><\/strong> or external, which doesn\u2019t have <strong>Azure Active Directory subscription<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>1. In your <strong>Lab<\/strong> click on <strong>Settings<\/strong>.<br \/>\n2. From the list of users, choose <strong>Users<\/strong> to add a new user.<br \/>\n3. Click on the <strong>Add button<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/1-1-add-new-user-in-devtest-labs\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6309\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6309\" title=\"1-1 Add new User in DevTest Labs\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-1-Add-new-User-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg\" alt=\"1-1 Add new User in DevTest Labs\" width=\"763\" height=\"404\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-1-Add-new-User-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg 966w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-1-Add-new-User-in-DevTest-Labs-300x159.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-1-Add-new-User-in-DevTest-Labs-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>4. In <strong>Add Access blade<\/strong> click on <strong>Select a role<\/strong>.<br \/>\n5. In <strong>Select a role blade<\/strong> click on <strong>DevTest Lab User<\/strong>.<br \/>\n6. When new blade appear click on <strong>Add Users<\/strong>.<br \/>\n7. Type the <strong>email address<\/strong> of the <strong>User<\/strong>, which can be also external user as long as he has valid <a href=\"https:\/\/www.microsoft.com\/en-us\/account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Microsoft Account<\/a>.<br \/>\n8. If this user has a valid <strong>Microsoft Account<\/strong>, the system will validate and it will be colored in blue color. Click on the blue user and confirm the entry by clicking on <strong>Select<\/strong> button.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/1-2-add-new-user-and-select-a-role-in-devtest-labs\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6310\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6310\" title=\"1-2 Add new User and Select a role in DevTest Labs\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-2-Add-new-User-and-Select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg\" alt=\"1-2 Add new User and Select a role in DevTest Labs\" width=\"763\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-2-Add-new-User-and-Select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg 965w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-2-Add-new-User-and-Select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs-300x159.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/1-2-Add-new-User-and-Select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span>If you would like to learn more about using different environments during the realization of a software system \u2013 have a look at the post <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/02\/22\/azure-devtest-labs-updates\/\">Azure DevTest Labs Updates<\/a>. <a href=\"https:\/\/azure.microsoft.com\/en-us\/services\/devtest-lab\/\">Azure DevTest Labs<\/a> is a service provided by Microsoft Azure which provides functionality for managing environments that contain <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-us\/azure\/virtual-machines\/\">Azure Virtual Machines<\/a>. The post, mentioned above, describes both the core capabilities of DevTest Labs and the new features of the service (as of February, 2018).<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Step 2\">Step 2: Add Owner in DevTest Labs<\/h3>\n<p><strong>DevTeb Labs<\/strong> does not allow to add the <strong>Owner<\/strong> role at the lab level as this is not currently supported. To add the <strong>Owner<\/strong> role, you will have to add it in <strong>Subscriptions<\/strong> of the lab. The <strong>Owner<\/strong> role has the full access to the all management and other functionalities in the lab.<\/p>\n<p>1. Navigate to <strong>Subscriptions<\/strong> of the lab.<br \/>\n2. Choose the right <strong>Subscription<\/strong> from the list.<br \/>\n3. Navigate to <strong>Settings<\/strong>.<br \/>\n4. Click on <strong>Users<\/strong> to add a new user.<br \/>\n5. Click on <strong>Add<\/strong> button.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/2-1-add-owner-in-devtest-labs\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6311\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6311\" title=\"2-1 Add Owner in DevTest Labs\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-1-Add-Owner-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg\" alt=\"2-1 Add Owner in DevTest Labs\" width=\"763\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-1-Add-Owner-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg 963w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-1-Add-Owner-in-DevTest-Labs-300x158.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-1-Add-Owner-in-DevTest-Labs-768x405.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>6. In <strong>Add access blade<\/strong> click on <strong>Select a Role<\/strong>.<br \/>\n7. In <strong>Select a role blade<\/strong> click on <strong>Owner<\/strong>.<br \/>\n8. In <strong>Add access blade<\/strong> click on <strong>Add users<\/strong>.<br \/>\n9. Type the <strong>e-mail address<\/strong> of <strong>Owner<\/strong>.<br \/>\n10. If this user has a valid <strong>Microsoft Account<\/strong>, the system will validate and it will be colored in blue color. Click on the blue user and confirm the entry by clicking on Select button.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/2-2-add-owner-and-select-a-role-in-devtest-labs\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6312\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6312\" title=\"2-2 Add Owner and select a role in DevTest Labs\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-2-Add-Owner-and-select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg\" alt=\"2-2 Add Owner and select a role in DevTest Labs\" width=\"763\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-2-Add-Owner-and-select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs.jpg 963w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-2-Add-Owner-and-select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs-300x159.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/06\/2-2-Add-Owner-and-select-a-role-in-DevTest-Labs-768x406.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Con\">Conclusion<\/h3>\n<p>You can secure your lab by adding and defining different roles. It is important to know also that the user that created <strong>VM<\/strong> gets automatically assigned to the <strong>Owner<\/strong> role on the created <strong>VM<\/strong>. This user can then all the actions that are offered in the lab. However, the creation of <strong>Virtual Machine<\/strong> is only allowed from the <strong>DevTest Labs account<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"gray\"><span class=\"ion-video\">Video<\/span>You can see <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=C0ecnvmdAuQ\">this video<\/a><\/strong>, if you would like to find more information about how to create Linux machine on Azure, we will select Ubuntu server and remote connect to it using Git bash and PuTTY, and we will see how to test that our connection is established using sudo command<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction Step 1: Add new User in DevTest Labs Step &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/06\/30\/devtest-labs-security-settings\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">DevTest Labs security settings<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","footnote